(3, 1, 'bbpress', 'bbp_topic_create', '<a href="http://localhost/tamrielfoundry/members/atropos/" title="Atropos" rel="nofollow">Atropos</a> started the topic <a href="http://localhost/tamrielfoundry/topic/code-of-conduct/" title="Tamriel Foundry Code of Conduct">Tamriel Foundry Code of Conduct</a> in the forum <a href="http://localhost/tamrielfoundry/forum/general/elder-scrolls-online-discussion/" title="Elder Scrolls Online Discussion">Elder Scrolls Online Discussion</a>', '<span><strong>Ten Commandments of Tamriel Foundry</strong></span>\r\nUpdated: June 30, 2013\r\nThese are the rules for participating in the Tamriel Foundry community. By electing to post on this site, you implicitly agree to abide by these rules. Ignorance is not a valid excuse. Depending on the severity and frequency with which you are in violation of this code of conduct your account is subject to suspension or closure at the sole discretion of our moderators. These guidelines are not intended to be oppressive, nor are we interested in censorship. The following rules are chosen to ensure that this wonderful community continues to grow and feature a quality of discourse of which we can all be proud. Thank you for participating in the Tamriel Foundry community.\r\n\r\n<strong>1.</strong><strong> </strong><strong><span>Thou Shalt Not Flame</span>.</strong> Even if you strongly hate the content of a post, and detest the individual to whom you’re responding so strongly that you dream of seeing an angry Dremora playing kickball with his internal organs, please exercise restraint and post without personal attacks. You are fully permitted to make rude facial expressions and socially unacceptable hand gestures as you press “submit”. If you feel that a post violates this code of conduct and wish to report it to a moderator, you may use the “report post” button. Please refrain from @mentioning moderators to attract their attention or publically condemning the violations of others. Falsely, needlessly, or repeatedly using this reporting feature is considered an offense just as grave as spam or spoof posting. Waste our moderators’ time, and they will waste you.\r\n\r\nYour behavior is judged not only on this site, but throughout the Elder Scrolls community. If you slander or libel Tamriel Foundry or our site staff on another website, forum, or by other public means, your membership at Tamriel Foundry forum may be terminated without notice.\r\n\r\n<strong>2.</strong><strong> </strong><strong><span>Thou Shalt Not Spam or Engage in Posting Wars</span>.</strong> Post it once, and post it nice, and please don’t ever post it twice (there’s a song there somewhere). Pick a forum, pick a message, and that’s that. Don’t post in every forum with the same message. If it’s a general post, use one of our general forums. If it’s specific to a faction or class… well, you get the idea. Do not embark on a personal mission to correct the spelling and/or grammar of others. Even if your corrections were valid, such posts will be deleted. Correcting typos or errors is the individual responsibility of the original poster and the moderators of this forum.\r\n\r\nThe unsolicited and arbitrary spamming of friendship requests, private messages, or guild invitations is considered an offense most reviled. Only extend the arm of friendship to those individuals with whom you genuinely identify on Tamriel Foundry, otherwise you’ll quickly get the boot. Oh, and you won’t be missed regardless of how many “friends” your profile claims you have.\r\n\r\nIt warms our hearts that you care about your post count and forum title here at Tamriel Foundry. But if we see you posting meaningless tripe to edge up the count, or using the forum for chitchat better suited to private messaging or a chat client, we’ll ask you to stop. Keep it up, and we’ll reset your post count to negative 500. Yeah, we’re evil like that.\r\n\r\n<strong>3.</strong><strong> </strong><strong><span>Thou Shalt Not Advertise</span>.</strong> We do not intend to serve as a linking service or a search engine for other sites. Links that wouldn’t be allowed anywhere on the forums (including user profiles and signatures) would be to links to sites (commercial OR personal) that have:\r\n\r\n	Pornographic, racist, or illegal materials, including game cheats, hacks, or torrents of copyrighted works.\r\n	Explicitly “for profit” sites. Specifically, websites that earn the poster a profit/commission or sites that give points for incoming links.\r\n	Sites containing excessive advertisement packages, popups, trojans, keyloggers, malware of any form, or any other malicious content.\r\n	Advertisment for item and/or gold farming, powerleveling, account auctions, or links to sites which engage in these activities.\r\n\r\n<strong>4.</strong><strong> </strong><strong><span>Thou Shalt Not Post Naughty Links or Graven Images</span>.</strong> While Tamriel Foundry is a predominately adult community, Elder Scrolls fandom is universal. We do not allow the posting of pornographic or otherwise sexually explicit content. Likewise, any content which violates the standing <a title="Elder Scrolls Online NDA" href="http://elderscrollsonline.com/en/legal/nda" rel="nofollow">non-disclosure agreement</a> (NDA) will be removed, and the poster may be reported to ZeniMax Online Studios at the discretion of site staff.\r\n\r\n<strong>5.</strong><strong> </strong><strong><span>Thou Shalt Not Pimp or Aid in the Pimping of Hacks or Cheats</span>.</strong> Hacks and cheats are 3rd party programs that allow you to alter the way a player interacts with a game. We do not support the use of such programs. You may not ask for help in creating a hack/cheat, or provide links to where such files can be downloaded. However, the morality of using such programs is sometimes discussed and we allow such topics of conversation (within reason), unless they violate any other rule. The advertisement and/or promotion of game exploits falls under this category of behavior, do not help other players break the game, especially not if they belong to an opposing faction!\r\n\r\n<strong>6.</strong><strong> </strong><strong><span>Thou Shalt Not Engage in Unnatural Bumping</span>.</strong> Our forums automatically “bump up” active threads, where the topic with the most recent reply goes to the top of the forum listing. If your topic is good, it will be responded to. If it’s responded to, it will undergo the process we call “natural bumping”. Natural bumping = good. Unnatural bumping = bad. Unnatural bumping is where someone posts, “I’m adding this to put this thread back at the top.” Do it, we slap your hand. Do it often, you pull back a bloody stump.\r\n\r\n<strong>7.</strong><strong> </strong><strong><span>Thou Shalt Not Spoof</span>.</strong> Don’t make up an account name designed to resemble another poster. If an account is registered that could be confused (unintentionally) for a moderator, admin, or ZeniMax Online developer we reserve the right to offer the member the ability to change the name to something else.  We reserve the right to close the account if that offer isn’t accepted. In general you are encouraged to use your main in-game character’s name as a username on the Forums.\r\n\r\nIf you are banned for any reason, don’t keep coming back with “Fred,” “Fred the Undead”, and “Fred Yet Again.” If you were banned, take it like a man… well, take it like a reasonable person, and accept your fate. We <strong>ban the person not the account,</strong> registering under a new nickname will result in that account also being banned. If you wish, you may appeal the account closure by contacting admin@tamrielfoundry.com. Oh, and for goodness sake, don’t make up additional accounts to respond to yourself. People who talk to themselves used to be burned at the stake as witches; at Tamriel Foundry we still hold to that belief system.\r\n\r\n<strong>8.</strong><strong> </strong><strong><span>Thou Shalt Not Get Territorial</span>.</strong> If you post or submit something to our site or forums — be it an article, a news item, a strategy guide, or a suggestion — it becomes the property of Tamriel Foundry. That means if we leave it in the forum, it is still your work, but we have rights to it as well. If we allow it to be present on the site or use it in any form, you agree that you have no financial claim against the site. We do not demand that items be exclusively ours, but once something it submitted to us for publication or posted in our forums, its removal is entirely at our discretion.\r\n\r\n<strong>9.</strong><strong> </strong><strong><span>Thou Shalt Accept the Admin’s Decisions</span>.</strong> We (Tamriel Foundry and its admins) reserve the right to ban (temporarily or permanently) or place on suspension any member without warning. We reserve the right to edit, move or remove any post made on Tamriel Foundry without warning or explanation. We reserve the right to edit any portion of a member profile without warning. You will accept all this gladly and with open arms because we do it with love.\r\n\r\n<strong>10.</strong><strong> </strong><strong><span>Thou Shalt Not Mention “Freedom of Speech”</span>.</strong><strong> </strong>Or we’ll vomit. All over your fancy armor, we promise you. This is a private forum, and you are our invited guests. The administrators have a tough job, trying to keep the forums clean and presentable while not willingly stifling open discussion. If a thread or post is locked or deleted, that was the necessary step to take in the judgment of the administrator. Please don’t bandy irrelevant constitutional law and hope to plead the case for less “censorship.” Don’t start a vote, don’t throw food, and don’t throw a hissy fit. Don’t light up torches and mob our central office; we don’t even have a central office. We do not censor, we exercise judgment and quality control on something in which we invest a lot of time and effort.  We only accept posts written in English. “Text-speak”, excessive slang and/or abbreviation, or unnecessary reliance on acronyms (regardless of their popularity) is not permitted. Posts which contain racist, sexist, political, or religious messages, or otherwise "stir the pot" regarding inflammatory social issues are not allowed and will be removed without notification.\r\n\r\n<strong><span>Legal Small Print</span>:</strong> Tamriel Foundry assumes no responsibility for the content of posts made by members or off site websites linked to on these forums.  We are not liable for any damage or distress post content may cause to an individual or their property.  We assume all members have read these forums rules and automatically agree to their terms and conditions. Users follow offsite links at their own risk. The recommended age for Tamriel Foundry participation is 17+.\r\n\r\nAnything we did not say above, we hereby say herein and henceforth. Verily, we reserve the right to amend these rules at our discretion and without notification. The onus is on the member to periodically check these rules for changes.', 'http://localhost/tamrielfoundry/topic/code-of-conduct/', 32, 22, '2013-08-04 03:10:57', 0, 0, 0, 0),
